docs.abstract: Conservatives have expressed concern that their views are stifled at colleges and universities, and the Trump administration has taken up their cause.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General Jeff Sessions made clear on Monday that the Justice Department will oppose colleges and universities that stifle free speech on campus, a cause championed by conservatives who say their voices are silenced in higher education.

headline.main: Sessions Says Justice Dept. Has Helped Preserve Free Speech on Campuses
headline.print_headline: Session Vows to Defend Free Speech Against Campus ‘Bullies’

docs.abstract: President Trump’s pugilistic approach to China could rupture relations for years to come.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s pugilistic approach to China could rupture relations for years to come.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is confident that the United States is winning its trade war with China. But on both sides of the Pacific, a bleaker recognition is taking hold: The world’s two largest economies are in the opening stages of a new economic Cold War, one that could persist well after Mr. Trump is out of office.

headline.main: Trump Has Put the U.S. and China on the Cusp of a New Cold War
headline.print_headline: Trump Leaves U.S. And China on Tip Of New Cold War

docs.abstract: President Trump said he has never used terms like “mentally retarded” or “dumb Southerner,” as he is quoted in Bob Woodward’s new book. But the record shows he has.
docs.snippet: President Trump said he has never used terms like “mentally retarded” or “dumb Southerner,” as he is quoted in Bob Woodward’s new book. But the record shows he has.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As President Trump tries to rebut the portrayal in the latest attention-grabbing book, he has denied not only saying the things attributed to him, but also that he has ever said anything like them. The problem for Mr. Trump is that, in some cases at least, the record shows that he has.

headline.main: ‘I Don’t Talk’ That Way, Trump Says. Except When He Does.
headline.print_headline: ‘I Don’t Talk’ That Way, The President Insists. Except When He Does.
